data.body:
Hello! In Node's remove_child implementation we see that NOTIFICATION_UNPARENTED is 'raised' before the child is actually unparented:

```
p_child->notification(NOTIFICATION_UNPARENTED);
data.children.remove(idx);
...
p_child->data.parent=NULL;
```

Is this by design? If so, what is the reasoning? I was trying to use it so that when a child is removed it signals its ex-parent to refresh some calculations that involve going through its siblings asking for some data. But the removed child is still part of the children list, making such refresh meaningless.

I'm using a workaround right now, but I thought I'd ask since I found it a bit weird.
